Some notes
###########


# An example way to run this web app. We will serve static contents with nginx
# and forward all other (catalyst)  requests to starman
    #Step 1: start starman webserver, listen to port 8001:
    /www/perllib/bin/starman -I/www/www-live/lib/ -I/www/perllib/lib/perl5 /www/www-live/pageapp.psgi --pid /www/www-live/log/starman.pid --port 8001 --error-log /www/www-live/log/starman.error.log --access-log /www/www-live/log/starman.access.log --daemonize

    #Step 2: Configure nginx:
    2a) Change localhost in pageapp.nginx.conf with the real server_name
    2b) You should add pageapp.nginx.conf to nginx 'sites-available' dir and symlink it in 'sites-enabled'. 
        These dirs are usually located in ' /etc/nginx/' on ubuntu systems where nginx has been installed.

    #Note that nginx expects ssl certificate and key here:
    /www/ssl/server.crt
    /www/ssl/server.key
    
    #Step 3: Start nginx as root as it needs to listen to port:80 and port:443
    Once started nginx will serve static contents. It will forward all others to port 8001.


# Session data directory:
The sessions are stored '/www/tmp/session'. This location is configurable via pageapp.yaml file.

# A crontab should clean up any old session data:
*/30 * * * * find /www/tmp/session/ -maxdepth 1 -type d -regex "/www/tmp/session/.+" -cmin +120 -exec rm -rf {} \;
